com.hoiio.api
Class FaxAPI

java.lang.Object
  com.hoiio.api.FaxAPI

public class FaxAPI
extends Object

Fax API provides developers access to faxing capabilities by using our simple API. Developers can use the Fax API to send, and also to receive fax via Hoiio virtual numbers.

Charges for fax is similar to our Voice API - by per minute usage. This should not come as a surprise since fax is delivered over phone lines.

Note that Fax is only supported in the following countries:

  • Singapore

getHistory

public static FaxHistory getHistory(HoiioAuth auth,
                                    FaxAPI.FaxType type,
                                    int page)
                             throws HttpPostConnectionException,
                                    HoiioRestException
This API will retrieve the history of faxes sent by this application.

Parameters:
auth - The user authorization object for the request
type - The type of history to retrieve
page - The page of the history to retrieve, starting from page 1
Returns:
The fax history specified by the parameters, starting at the first entry specified in @page with at most 100 entries
Throws:
HttpPostConnectionException - if there is a connection failure
HoiioRestException - if there were problems using this REST API
See Also:
http://developer.hoiio.com/docs/fax_history.html

sendFax

public static String sendFax(HoiioAuth auth,
                             String sender,
                             String dest,
                             String filepath,
                             String filename)
                      throws HttpPostConnectionException,
                             HoiioRestException
Sends a fax specified by the method parameters

Parameters:
auth - The user authorization object for the request
sender - The sender number or caller id to be displayed
dest - The destination to send the fax to. Phone numbers should start with a "+" and country code (E.164 format), e.g. +6511111111.
filepath - The path of the fax to be sent
filename - The file name of the fax desired
Returns:
A unique reference ID for this fax transaction. This parameter will not be present if the request was not successful.
Throws:
HttpPostConnectionException - if there is a connection failure
HoiioRestException - if there were problems using this REST API
See Also:
http://developer.hoiio.com/docs/fax_send.html
